<div class="PhorumReadBodySubject"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-2">Ship ownership</kw></div>
<div class="PhorumReadBodyHead"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">Posted by: </kw><strong><a href="http://www.piratesinfo.com/mysql/phorum/profile.php?1,1482"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">ladycozzette</kw></a></strong><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1"> (---.metrocast.net)</kw></div>
<div class="PhorumReadBodyHead"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">Date: 17 September 2004, 10:20PM</kw></div>
<br>
<div class="PhorumReadBodyText"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3"> I have searched and the other threads really dont seem to answer my question.  One comment may hvae in a round about way, but if so I didn't catch it. I also quickly searched online but I only found tuff about after the pirates were through with the ship.
</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
If a ships captain was elected, who owned the ship? Did the crew?
</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
 Did the ship change hands as they changed captains?
</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
If the crew votes for a new captain is that still mutiny?
</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
Is the Quartermaster the same as a first mate, or are there clear distinctions (many sites seemed to say the same things for both in different ways)?
</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
 Many sites said that crews typicaly chose one or the other, but could there have been both?</kw></div><br>
</div>


