<div class="PhorumStdBlock">
<div class="PhorumReadBodySubject"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-2">Re: Ship ownership</kw></div>
<div class="PhorumReadBodyHead"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">Posted by: </kw><strong><a href="http://www.piratesinfo.com/mysql/phorum/profile.php?1,1696"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">Aaron Whifflingpin</kw></a></strong><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1"> (---.winn.dial.virgin.net)</kw></div>
<div class="PhorumReadBodyHead"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">Date: 17 November 2004, 04:19PM</kw></div>
<br>
<div class="PhorumReadBodyText"> 
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
Since pirates generally stole their ships, they probably avoided the question of "ownership" all together.  
</kw><br>
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
I think, from a quick browse of Johnson, that the whole crew owned the ship if it was a question of sharing out the prize money, but the Captain generally made the decisions about keeping, changing or scuttling ships.
</kw><br>
<br>
<br>
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
Fetch aft the rum, Darby</kw></div><br>
</div>


