<div class="PhorumStdBlock">
<div class="PhorumReadBodySubject"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-2">Re: Ship ownership</kw></div>
<div class="PhorumReadBodyHead"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">Posted by: </kw><strong><a href="http://www.piratesinfo.com/mysql/phorum/profile.php?1,6"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">Foxe</kw></a></strong><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1"> (---.winn.dial.virgin.net)</kw></div>
<div class="PhorumReadBodyHead"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">Date: 18 November 2004, 01:56PM</kw></div>
<br>
<div class="PhorumReadBodyText"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3"> Ah, you clearly answered before looking at the thread quoted! It is not so much the duties of the Quartermaster, Master, mates, Boatswain or any other rank which confuses me - they are relatively clear in general even if not strictly defined. What plagues me is the question of why a Quartermaster should hold such a high position on a pirate ship (2IC) as some evidence suggests, when they held a relatively low one on almost any other ship.
</kw><br>
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">
.</kw><br>
<br>
<br>
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">
Foxe
</kw><br>
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">
