<div class="PhorumStdBlock">
<div class="PhorumReadBodySubject"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-2">Re: Ship ownership</kw></div>
<div class="PhorumReadBodyHead"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">Posted by: </kw><strong><a href="http://www.piratesinfo.com/mysql/phorum/profile.php?1,6"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">Foxe</kw></a></strong><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1"> (---.winn.dial.virgin.net)</kw></div>
<div class="PhorumReadBodyHead"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">Date: 18 November 2004, 06:52PM</kw></div>
<br>
<div class="PhorumReadBodyText"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3"> So, it begs the question (and this is not another bells thread!), apart from Captain Roberts' articles quoted in Johnson, what evidence is there that the Quartermaster was second in command under the Captain?
</kw><br>
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
Whenever someone asks about pirate ranks on this board someone immediately says "Captain, then Quartermaster...etc", but is that actually accurate?
</kw><br>
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
I am genuinely intrigued by this problem and have been for some time, so please indulge me - if there is more evidence let's share it, if there isn't then let's rethink our stock answers.
</kw><br>
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">
.</kw><br>
<br>
<br>
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">
Foxe
</kw><br>
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">
Historian,  Pirate Dogmatist, Destroyer of Buckets</kw></div><br>
</div>


