<div class="PhorumReadMessageBlock">
<div class="PhorumStdBlock">
<div class="PhorumReadBodySubject"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-2">Re: Ship ownership</kw></div>
<div class="PhorumReadBodyHead"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">Posted by: </kw><strong><a href="http://www.piratesinfo.com/mysql/phorum/profile.php?1,1321"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">Silver Steele</kw></a></strong><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1"> (---.ec.rr.com)</kw></div>
<div class="PhorumReadBodyHead"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1">Date: 18 November 2004, 08:52PM</kw></div>
<br>
<div class="PhorumReadBodyText"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-2"> Ed Low's articles:
</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
The captain is to have two full shares, the master is to have one share and a half, the doctor, mate, gunner, and boatswain, one share and a quarter.
</kw><br>
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-2">
George Lowther's articles:
</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
The Captain is to have two full shares; the Master is to have one Share and a half; the Doctor, Mate, Gunner &amp; Boatswain, one Share and a quarter. 
</kw><br>
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-2">
John Phillips' articles:
</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
Every man shall obey civil Command; the Captain shall have one full Share and a half Prizes; the Master, Carpenter, Boatswain and Gunner shall have one Share and quarter. 
</kw><br>
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-2">
B. Roberts' articles:
</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
The captain and the quartermaster shall each receive two shares of a prize, the master gunner and boatswain, one and one half shares, all other officers one and one quarter, and private gentlemen of fortune one share each.</kw><br>
<br>
<br>
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
~When your a professional pirate, you don't have to wear a suit.... Now if only my boss agreed with that....~</kw></div><br>
