<br>
<div class="PhorumReadBodyText"><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3"> Back to "ship ownership:"
</kw><br>
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
Pre-Golden Age, when piracy was largely an accepted extension of commerce, the ship was often owned by a consortium of land-based backers.
</kw><br>
<br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3">
For example, Queen Elizabeth I was sometimes part-owner (purely as a private person, of course) when Drake went a-pirating.</kw></div><br>
</div>


